	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93989><span id=Scholar>KlissarSilverspine</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>45 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.88]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The flamberge from tunare is certainly a nice weapon, but unfortunately the root proc ruins it for most people.<br><br>Provided you actually were fighting a mob that isn't immune to run speed changes, when the heartwood flamberge procs, the mob turns to whomever is closest... and for some reason rogues and monks always like to have their heads right up the mobs' arses.&nbsp;&nbsp;In a place like BoT or PoTactics, this can quickly turn into a dead group, especially if it happens just as a mob enrages.<br><br>If the mob is immune (as most &quot;boss&quot; mobs are) to root then you end up getting a VERY large amount of aggro.  You go splat because I can assure you that they're not going to break a CH chain to heal a pally/sk that can't control their aggro.<br><br>The 3 people in my guild that have the flamberge wish the arch lich would drop a blindfoe or sword of the lost crusades so they could have a comparable damage weapon for everyday use.<br><br>Klissar Silverspine ~ Dread Lord of Greenmist<br>The Nameless</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
